  "summary": "At Miss Blacklock's home, Patrick, Julia, and Philippa discuss the household preparations. Miss Blacklock, who prefers to handle tasks herself, prepares for unexpected visitors. Patrick moves a tray of sherry and snacks to a bay window to maintain the appearance of a quiet evening. After Patrick brings a new bottle of sherry from the kitchen, the doorbell rings, confirming Miss Blacklock's intuition that guests would arrive.\n\nA series of neighbors arrive: Colonel Eastbrook and his wife, who mention their lack of central heating; Miss Inchclyde and Miss Muggleton from the Gravel Pits, who discuss duck eggs and chrysanthemums; and Mrs. Swetnam and Edmund, who offer Miss Blacklock a kitten and note the use of central heating. During the visit, Colonel Eastbrook expresses his belief that war is inevitable.\n\nThe final guest, Mrs. Harmon, arrives and jokingly asks if she is too late for \"the murder.\" She discusses her husband Julian's recent sermon, which was inspired by a mystery book titled *The Hat Trick of Death*. As the group waits for the anticipated event, Miss Blacklock suggests they have sherry. As the mantelpiece clock begins to chime at 6:15, the room falls silent. Just as the final chime of the sequence fades, all the lights in the house go out.",
